comment_data.body:
`Py_FatalError` looks like it's in the Stable ABI:

https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/9181d776daf87f0e4e2ce02c08f162150fdf7d79/Misc/stable_abi.toml#L1630-L1631
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -582,8 +582,22 @@ typedef uintptr_t  __pyx_uintptr_t;
   #endif
 #endif
 
+#ifdef Py_UNREACHABLE
+  #define __Pyx_UNREACHABLE() Py_UNREACHABLE()
+#elif __Pyx_has_cbuiltin(__builtin_unreachable)
+  #define __Pyx_UNREACHABLE() __builtin_unreachable()
+#elif defined(__clang__) || defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || (defined(__GNUC__) && (__GNUC__ > 4 || (__GNUC__ == 4 && __GNUC_MINOR__ >= 5)))
+  #define __Pyx_UNREACHABLE() __builtin_unreachable()
+#elif defined(_MSC_VER)
+  #define __Pyx_UNREACHABLE() __assume(0)
+#elif !CYTHON_COMPILING_IN_LIMITED_API
+  #define __Pyx_UNREACHABLE() Py_FatalError("Unreachable C code path reached")

comment_data.body:
According to the [documentation](https://docs.python.org/3/c-api/unicode.html#c.PyUnicode_Equal):

> The function always succeeds if a and b are str objects.

which I think should be true in the usage here? I don't know if that's enough justification to skip the check.

The comment won't be true for bytearrays though.

I think it works though because they're guaranteed to be `/0` terminated but the reason isn't right.

commit.message: Integrate optimised str comparisons into general object comparisons.
Adapt test (not sure if it tests the right tree paths).
Add str comparison benchmark.
Character comparison needs to be signed.
Allow tempita substitution in utility code dependencies by providing a JSON context dict.
Replace the existing "StringTools.c::UnicodeEquals" utility with the new str-str object comparison utility.
Include bytes.
Include bytearray and cross comparison with bytes.
Benchmarks: directly compare the last steps: only int/float with str, with bytes, with bytearray.
Only use mixed case if it's not obviously excluded.
Benchmarks: Include 'bytearray' in fused types.
Fix benchmark config.
Avoid "unused label" C compiler warning.
Fix temporary benchmark config.
Remove dead code.
Enable optimised bytes comparison in Limited API.
Fix signedness in comparison of first byte.
Include str/bytes/bytearray in tests.
Do not call str-str comparison in Limited API.
Fix template syntax.
Fix return pointer type for PyBytes_AsStringAndSize().
Fix C-API usage for bytearray.
Use longer strings and less initial overhead in comparison benchmark.
Try to make the benchmarks run a little quicker.
Allow the microbenchmarks to scale more accurately.
Split str-str comparison code by character size to allow independent C loop optimisation.
Try to make the benchmarks run a little quicker.
Define a macro for "__has_builtin" checks that also works on compilers that don't provide __has_builtin().
Use new "__Pyx_has_cbuiltin" macro.
Borrow from CPython's str comparison code to avoid a performance regression when comparing long strings.
Refactor str-str comparison cases into a single switch statement.
Merge branch 'master' into str_cmp
Implement str-str comparison for the Limited API.
Use Py_FatalError() as general fallback for __Pyx_UNREACHABLE().
Minor cleanups.
Avoid PyUnicode_READ() in favour of direct casts.
Use PyUnicode_Compare().
Benchmarks: Remove additional git IDs that were used for comparison.
Undo whitespace change.
Merge branch 'master' into str_cmp
